In article <304qvm$9cj@northshore.ecosoft.com> ws@northshore.ecosoft.com (William Stallings) writes:

>There is a scheme called LUC developed by a group in New Zealand. There 
>is some question as to how much of the original development was done by 
>them and how much was borrowed, but in any case it differs from RSA. It 
>is based on the use of Lucas sequences. The January 1993 Dr Dobb's 
>Journal has a description, as does my book, Network and Internetwork 
>Security (Prentic-hall/Macmillan, ISBN 0-02-415483-0).

The paper on LUC by Smith and Lennon is also available as:
   ftp.informatik.uni-hamburg.de:/pub/virus/texts/crypto/luc.zip

This (unzipped) is a postscript file.

